<p>I am using the following Ant script with username and IP address. I want to transfer a file. If username has a space in it, the file is not transferring.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;project name="Hello World Project" default="info"&gt;   &lt;property file="build.properties"/&gt;   &lt;target name="info"&gt;     &lt;scp file="/home/smith/Gjs/ws2/abc.txt"       todir="Srupanan kumar:rakesh@19.1.21.6:~/" trust="true"/&gt;   &lt;/target&gt; &lt;/project&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there any way to use <code>&lt;scp&gt;</code> with a username containing a space?</p>